SentinelOne — features you use daily

1. Threat detection — how S1 finds threats
Static AI
Scans files before they execute — like antivirus but smarter. Uses ML to detect malicious files.
Behavioral AI
Watches what programs DO — not just what they are. Catches unknown/zero-day malware.
2. Threat severity levels you see in S1
Suspicious
— Needs your investigation. Could be real or false positive.
Malicious
— Confirmed threat. S1 may have already blocked it.
Critical
— Active attack in progress. Escalate to L2 immediately.
3. Storyline — S1's killer feature
What Storyline does
SentinelOne automatically links all related events on an endpoint into one visual story. Instead of 47 separate alerts, you see ONE incident showing: which file started it, what processes ran, what registry keys changed, what network connections were made — all in chronological order. This is what makes investigation fast.
4. Response actions available to you
Isolate endpoint
Cuts machine from all network. EDR connection stays alive. Use when confirmed infected.
Remediate
Deletes the malicious file and all associated artifacts from the system.
Rollback
Undoes ALL changes malware made — restores deleted files, removes registry keys, reverts settings. Like a time machine.
Kill process
Terminates a running malicious process immediately without full isolation.
Hash blacklist
Blocks a specific malicious file hash across ALL endpoints in your environment instantly.
Deep Visibility
Query tool — search across all endpoint telemetry. Like Google search for your endpoint data.
5. Deep Visibility — your forensic search tool
Deep Visibility is like being able to search every CCTV footage from every machine in the company at once. You type a query like "show me all machines that ran PowerShell in the last 24 hours" — and it finds them instantly.
Example Deep Visibility queries you would run
— "Find all endpoints that communicated with IP 185.234.x.x"
— "Which machines ran mimikatz.exe in the last 7 days?"
— "Show all PowerShell executions from non-system accounts today"
— "Find files with hash abc123 across all endpoints"
SentinelOne's biggest advantage over competitors: Rollback. No other major EDR can undo malware changes as automatically and completely as S1. Always mention this in interviews.




